<p>
<seg id=1> The US and North Korea continued their meetings on Friday regarding allowing US inspectors being allowed into one nuclear facility located not far from Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=2> Both sides representatives are going to hold two days of meetings in New York, then continue their meeting in Washington. </seg>
<seg id=3> Last month both sides held a similar meeting in Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=4> That meeting was announced to be broken off because North Korea proposed a request. </seg>
<seg id=5> North Korea requested that the US provide 300,000,000 US dollars as an exchange for allowing the inspectors access. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before holding the new talks, North Korea made serious criticisms towards the US. </seg>
</p>
